transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Biagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yeah, this is Leo Velez.

Speaker 1: I ordered the new Biagra, A-V-B, or whatever the thing is.

Speaker 2: And I got a generic Biagra.

Speaker 1: That's not what I ordered.

Speaker 2: Okay. Let me take a look into your account.

Speaker 1: What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 2: Yeah, the name is Velez.

Speaker 1: Last name is V-E-L-E-Z.

Speaker 2: Yeah, and your zip code?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's 07734.

Speaker 2: Okay. So, I pulled you up here.

Speaker 1: Let me see what's going on here.

Speaker 2: Quick question.

Speaker 1: Do you have the bottle near you so you can just take a look

Speaker 2: at the pill real quick and tell me what it says on there?

Speaker 1: On the pill itself?

Speaker 2: Yeah, the engraving on the pill.

Speaker 1: I just wanted to confirm one thing because there's supposed

Speaker 2: to be a certain marking on the pill.

Speaker 1: Okay. So, you're saying that the label is wrong?

Speaker 2: No, I'm not saying the label is wrong.

Speaker 1: I just asked what the pill says on the pill.

Speaker 2: It says AC333.

Speaker 1: 339. AC339.

Speaker 2: Yeah. All right.

Speaker 1: So with that information,

Speaker 2: it confirmed the pharmacy didn't make a mistake.

Speaker 1: The only marking you should have seen

Speaker 2: on your pill is 50 for the dosage, and that's it.

Speaker 1: I'm going to go ahead and notify them and let them know

Speaker 2: that you're actually going to be not taking those

Speaker 1: because they sent the wrong one.

Speaker 2: And you'll receive the new order in three to four business days.

Speaker 1: Other than that, these new pills are going to say 50 on there.

Speaker 2: That's how you can identify it's the AGV.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: So what do I do with these?

Speaker 1: Do I put them back?

Speaker 2: No, you just keep them, dispose of them.

Speaker 1: It's up to you.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: So you're saying in three days, I should get the pill guy away?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: And your name is?

Speaker 2: Joe, J-O.

Speaker 1: Just Joe, huh?

Speaker 2: No last name?

Speaker 1: Joe?

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, no, no last name, but like my, I'm the only Joe

Speaker 1: in the office, so you'll be able to find me pretty quickly.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I hope you guys aren't running a scam.

Speaker 2: Well, if we were, why would I offer to send you the right stuff?

Speaker 1: I would just tell you that you got the right stuff.

Speaker 2: All right, Joe.

Speaker 1: I'm taking you for your word.

Speaker 2: Thanks a lot, man.

Speaker 1: No problem, sir.

Speaker 2: You have a great day now.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
